ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Summary of course material:All of Atiyah/ Macdonald's Commutative Algebra.I highly recommend the course
A must take class for graduate student.
I would absolutely recommend this class to other students. It's a wonderful introduction to algebraic geometry with lots of elaboration on the material in the book.
I would recommend it to someone who has a solid background in abstract algebra, and not to someone who hasn't.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: Aside the fact that I understand more on ring theory, it helps me to get into the world of algebraic geometry which I think it would play a big role in algebraic number theory
Commutative algebra is an important subject for me, so I'm glad I had agood course on it.
Not relevant to my dissertation/research, personally.
